# React Component Patterns

- Use function components with explicit props types.
- Use named exports for components, hooks, and utilities.
- Keep components small and focused; extract subcomponents instead of nesting deeply.
- Avoid deeply nested ternaries; use early returns.
- Avoid inline complex business logic in JSX.

## Hooks and Side Effects

- Put shared hooks in `src/shared/hooks`.
- Put feature hooks in `src/features/<feature>/hooks`.
- Keep side effects in handlers/hooks, not mixed into presentational components.

## Next.js Component Guidance

- Server Components by default.
- Add `'use client'` only when using client-only APIs (state, effects, browser APIs, event handlers).
- Keep client boundaries narrow and local.

## UI Composition

- Reuse shared building blocks from `src/shared/components`.
- Keep feature-specific UI under `src/features/<feature>/components`.
